Hello community, I need help. I have created a module and inserted the form. On a landing page I am using that module, now I want to customize the form with CSS, does anyone have an example or a guide?
```&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  hbspt.forms.create({
    region: "xxx",
    portalId: "xxx",
    formId: "{{ xxxx }}"
  });
&lt;/script&gt;```

Hey <@U07CK7UER34>,
you can add a cssClass to the code like this
```&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  hbspt.forms.create({
    region: "xxx",
    portalId: "xxx",
    formId: "{{ xxxx }}",
    cssClass: "myClass"
  });
&lt;/script&gt;```
and add your custom styling to it in a CSS file like theme-overrides.css

Also - here's the whole guide on <https://developers.HubSpot.com/beta-docs/reference/cms/forms|form embed code modification>
